    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hallucination is confident generation of false or unsupported content—fake citations, invalid API parameters, or invented tool results. Agents amplify risk because errors trigger downstream actions (payments, deletes, emails). Mitigation combines grounding, verification, and constrained decoding."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The model optimizes plausible continuations, not truth. Without grounding, it fabricates details that fit linguistic context—especially for rare entities or precise numbers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A hallucinated SQL WHERE clause or customer ID causes real damage. Trust boundaries must treat model output as untrusted input until validated."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mitigations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RAG",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — retrieve evidence; require citations"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tool grounding",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — fetch authoritative data via APIs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Validators",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — JSON schema, SQL parsers, allowlists"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Human approval",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — for high-impact actions"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Logprobs / confidence",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — flag low-confidence tokens where supported"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom jsonschema import validate\n\nSCHEMA = {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\"action\": {\"enum\": [\"search\", \"none\"]}, \"query\": {\"type\": \"string\"}},\n    \"required\": [\"action\"],\n}\n\nraw = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Return JSON plan only.\"}],\n    response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n).choices[0].message.content\n\ndata = json.loads(raw)\nvalidate(instance=data, schema=SCHEMA)  # reject hallucinated shape before tools run"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Hallucination is structural—models optimize fluency, not truth"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agents need validators and tools before side effects"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Structured outputs reduce format hallucinations, not factual ones"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Design workflows assuming some fraction of outputs are wrong"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
